AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Client for this installation.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Name
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A non-unique identifier for a record/document often used as a search tool.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A more descriptive identifier (that does need to be unique) of a record/document that is used as a default search option along with the search key (that is unique and mostly shorter). It is up to 60 characters in length.

AD_FIELD.NAME: UOM
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A non monetary unit of measure.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The UOM defines a unique non monetary unit of measure

AD_FIELD.NAME: Tax Category
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A classification of tax options based on similar characteristics or attributes.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Tax Category provides a method of grouping similar taxes. For example, Sales Tax or Value Added Tax.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Template Location
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The location of the template
AD_FIELD.HELP: Set up the location of the jasper template in your system

AD_FIELD.NAME: Product Category
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A classification of items based on similar characteristics or attributes.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Identifies the category which this product belongs to. Product categories are used for pricing.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Client for this installation.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Purchase
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An indication that an item may be purchased by a business partner.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Purchased check box indicates if this product is purchased by this organization.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Product Revenue
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An account number in the general ledger to mark transactions with this product.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Product Revenue Account indicates the account used for recording sales revenue for this product.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Product COGS
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The cost of goods sold for a specified product.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Product COGS Account indicates the account used when recording costs associated with this product.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Document Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A value defining what sequence and process setup are used to handle this document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Document Type determines document sequence and processing rules

AD_FIELD.NAME: Production
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An indication that an item is being used in production.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A product that is used for production plans

AD_FIELD.NAME: Product Asset
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A tangible asset used for business without expectation of sale in the coming fiscal year.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Product Asset Account indicates the account used for valuing this a product in inventory.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Search Key
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A fast method for finding a particular record.
AD_FIELD.HELP:
A search key allows for a fast method of finding a particular record. If you leave the search key empty, the system automatically creates a numeric number originating from a document sequence defined in the "Document Sequence" window. The sequence naming convention follows a rule "DocumentNo_TableName", where TableName is the actual name of the database table (e.g. C_Order).
Usually, company's internal identifiers for various records (products, customers, etc) are stored here.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Stocked
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Organization stocks this product
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Stocked check box indicates if this product is stocked by this Organization.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Product Expense
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An account number in the general ledger to mark transactions with this item.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Product Expense Account indicates the account used to record expenses associated with this product.

AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Commercial Name of the Business Partner
AD_FIELD.HELP: Commercial Name of the Business Partner

AD_FIELD.NAME: Product Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An important classification used to determine the accounting and management of a product.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are four types of products available. Item type can be used to configure any product such as raw materials or finished products ready to be sold. An item can be flagged as Socked or not, can be part of a production process and/or can be a bill of materials. Item type is the only one for which a cost type calculation can be configured. Service type can be used to configure consultancy, transport or insurance services. Service type can be purchased or sold but can not be stocked. A service can be a bill of materials. Finally Resource and Expense are product types which can be used to distinguish between different types of products which can be purchased or sold but make not sense to stock. Expense type can be used to configure travel expenses fto be used while reporting Employee Expenses. The fact of using a given product type does not mean a different accounting. All product types account same way while being purchased, stocked or sold. All of them use the ledger accounts defined in the Accounting tab of the Product window.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Window
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A work area which can be used to create, view, edit, and process a record.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Window field identifies a unique Window in the system.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Bill of Materials
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Bill of Materials
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Bill of Materials check box indicates if this product consists of a bill of materials.
